606 likes, 8 comments - rememberingyugoslavia on May 4, 2023: "On the 25th of May 1980, three weeks after the native son Josip Broz Tito's death, 43 years ago today, the good people of Zagorje and Zagreb planted 88 red maples 1Ô∏è‚É£ along this road, and erected a plaque on a rock to commemorate the deed 2Ô∏è‚É£. 
.
The intention was for each tree to represent one year of his life. But Tito died three days short of his 88th birthday. The trees still grow along the alley, since renamed to Josip Broz Street (that is minus "Tito"), but there are only 87 of them. One grew stunted and later a car crashed into it so it had to be replaced. The replant dried out.*
